{
  "texts": [
    "If writing as a process consists of the stages of \"prewriting, planning, drafting, revising, and editing\" (Strobl et al., 2019, p. 38), then AWE and AWCF are mostly used in the latter two stages.",
    "Our previous research revealed, however, that rephrasing tools such as Wordtune are used both in improving text at the revision stage, but also in breaking through mental blocks in the early stages of writing or even planning (Zhao et al., 2023).",
    "Similarly, Malik et al. (2023) found Indonesian students also using a wide range of AI-based tools in their writing.",
    "Translation tools might also be used at various stages, such as in processing reading and drafting text (Zhao et al., 2024).",
    "So just as writing is a complex iterative process, the use of digital writing tools is complex."
  ]
}